    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Retrieval Source Provenance for RAG Pipelines"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A RAG pipeline that cannot tell you which document a Claude response was grounded in is ungovernable at enterprise scale. Source provenance answers the auditor's question — \"where did this AI claim come from?\" — and the data governance team's question: \"if we retract document X, which AI outputs are now unsupported?\" Building provenance into a RAG pipeline from the start is far cheaper than retrofitting it after a compliance incident."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "RAG pipeline provenance flow diagram",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The diagram shows how provenance metadata flows through every stage: source documents are ingested with stable IDs and content hashes, metadata is preserved through chunking and embedding into the vector store, retrieved chunks carry their source IDs into context assembly, and the full provenance chain is recorded in an immutable store."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Provenance Metadata Requirements"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Every chunk that can reach Claude's context window must carry a provenance record with enough information to trace back to the original source and version."
          }
        ]
      },
