      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Never discard provenance metadata at the chunking or embedding step. Storing it in the vector database alongside the embedding costs negligible space and is the only link between retrieved text and the original document."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Instrumenting the Ingestion Pipeline"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Provenance begins at ingest. Each document entering the knowledge base must receive a stable source_id and have its chunks fingerprinted before embeddings are generated."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Document Ingester with Provenance"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import hashlib, uuid, json\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, asdict\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n@dataclass\nclass ProvenanceRecord:\n    source_id: str\n    source_uri: str\n    source_version: str\n    chunk_id: str\n    chunk_index: int\n    content_hash: str\n    ingest_timestamp: str\n    acl: list[str]\n    classification: str\n    text: str          # kept for re-indexing; omit from lineage logs if sensitive\n\ndef chunk_document(text: str, source_id: str, source_uri: str,\n                   source_version: str, acl: list[str],\n                   classification: str,\n                   chunk_size: int = 512) -> list[ProvenanceRecord]:\n    \"\"\"Split text into overlapping chunks, each with provenance metadata.\"\"\"\n    words = text.split()\n    overlap = chunk_size // 4\n    chunks = []\n    i = 0\n    idx = 0\n    while i < len(words):\n        chunk_words = words[i : i + chunk_size]\n        chunk_text = \" \".join(chunk_words)\n        chunk_id = f\"{source_id}#chunk-{idx:04d}\"\n        chunks.append(ProvenanceRecord(\n            source_id=source_id,\n            source_uri=source_uri,\n            source_version=source_version,\n            chunk_id=chunk_id,\n            chunk_index=idx,\n            content_hash=hashlib.sha256(chunk_text.encode()).hexdigest(),\n            ingest_timestamp=datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),\n            acl=acl,\n            classification=classification,\n            text=chunk_text,\n        ))\n        i += chunk_size - overlap\n        idx += 1\n    return chunks\n\ndef ingest_document(uri: str, text: str, version: str,\n                    acl: list[str], classification: str) -> list[ProvenanceRecord]:\n    source_id = str(uuid.uuid5(uuid.NAMESPACE_URL, uri))\n    chunks = chunk_document(text, source_id, uri, version, acl, classification)\n    return chunks\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Storing Chunks with Metadata in a Vector Database"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Using Chroma as an example; same pattern works with Pinecone, Weaviate, pgvector\nimport chromadb\nfrom sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer\n\nencoder = SentenceTransformer(\"all-MiniLM-L6-v2\")\nclient = chromadb.PersistentClient(path=\"./chroma_db\")\ncollection = client.get_or_create_collection(\"knowledge_base\")\n\ndef index_chunks(chunks: list[ProvenanceRecord]):\n    texts = [c.text for c in chunks]\n    embeddings = encoder.encode(texts).tolist()\n    collection.add(\n        ids=[c.chunk_id for c in chunks],\n        embeddings=embeddings,\n        documents=texts,\n        metadatas=[{\n            \"source_id\": c.source_id,\n            \"source_uri\": c.source_uri,\n            \"source_version\": c.source_version,\n            \"content_hash\": c.content_hash,\n            \"ingest_timestamp\": c.ingest_timestamp,\n            \"acl\": json.dumps(c.acl),          # Chroma metadata must be scalar or str\n            \"classification\": c.classification,\n        } for c in chunks],\n    )\n    print(f\"Indexed {len(chunks)} chunks from source {chunks[0].source_id}\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Access-Controlled Retrieval"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Provenance metadata enables access-controlled retrieval: a user can only receive chunks their ACL permits. Without this, a RAG pipeline leaks data across permission boundaries whenever two users share the same vector store."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def retrieve_with_acl(\n    query: str,\n    user_roles: list[str],\n    top_k: int = 5,\n) -> list[dict]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Retrieve chunks the requesting user is permitted to see.\n    Returns chunks with full provenance metadata attached.\n    \"\"\"\n    query_embedding = encoder.encode([query]).tolist()[0]\n\n    # Retrieve more candidates than needed so we have room to filter\n    results = collection.query(\n        query_embeddings=[query_embedding],\n        n_results=top_k * 4,\n        include=[\"documents\", \"metadatas\", \"distances\"],\n    )\n\n    permitted = []\n    for doc, meta, dist in zip(\n        results[\"documents\"][0],\n        results[\"metadatas\"][0],\n        results[\"distances\"][0],\n    ):\n        chunk_acl = json.loads(meta[\"acl\"])\n        if any(role in chunk_acl for role in user_roles):\n            permitted.append({\n                \"text\": doc,\n                \"source_id\": meta[\"source_id\"],\n                \"chunk_id\": meta.get(\"chunk_id\", \"\"),\n                \"source_uri\": meta[\"source_uri\"],\n                \"source_version\": meta[\"source_version\"],\n                \"content_hash\": meta[\"content_hash\"],\n                \"similarity_score\": round(1 - dist, 4),\n                \"classification\": meta[\"classification\"],\n            })\n        if len(permitted) == top_k:\n            break\n\n    return permitted\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Injecting Citation Markers into Context"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "To allow Claude to cite its sources, inject retrieved chunks with citation markers before passing them to the API. Instruct Claude in the system prompt to reference these markers when making factual claims."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def build_cited_context(chunks: list[dict]) -> tuple[str, dict[str, str]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns (context_block, citation_map) where citation_map maps\n    marker like '[1]' to source_id.\n    \"\"\"\n    lines = []\n    citation_map: dict[str, str] = {}\n    for i, chunk in enumerate(chunks, start=1):\n        marker = f\"[{i}]\"\n        citation_map[marker] = chunk[\"source_id\"]\n        lines.append(f\"{marker} (source: {chunk['source_uri']}, \"\n                     f\"score: {chunk['similarity_score']}):\\n{chunk['text']}\")\n    return \"\\n\\n\".join(lines), citation_map\n\nSYSTEM_PROMPT = \"\"\"You are a helpful assistant. Answer questions using only\nthe provided context passages. When you make a factual claim drawn from a\ncontext passage, cite it with its marker, e.g. [1] or [2]. If no passage\nsupports a claim, say you do not have that information.\"\"\"\n\ndef rag_call(query: str, user_roles: list[str]) -> dict:\n    import anthropic\n    chunks = retrieve_with_acl(query, user_roles)\n    context_block, citation_map = build_cited_context(chunks)\n\n    client = anthropic.Anthropic()\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-opus-4-8\",\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        system=SYSTEM_PROMPT,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": f\"Context passages:\\n{context_block}\\n\\nQuestion: {query}\"}],\n    )\n    return {\n        \"answer\": response.content[0].text,\n        \"citation_map\": citation_map,\n        \"source_chunks\": chunks,\n    }\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Claim-to-Source Mapping"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "After the response is generated, parse the citation markers from the output text and build an explicit claim-to-source mapping. This is the artefact a compliance officer can inspect to verify that each assertion in an AI response is traceable to an authorised document."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import re\n\ndef extract_claim_sources(response_text: str, citation_map: dict[str, str],\n                           chunks: list[dict]) -> list[dict]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Return a list of {claim_sentence, marker, source_id, source_uri, chunk_id}\n    for every sentence in the response that contains a citation marker.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Build chunk lookup by source_id for fast access\n    chunk_by_source = {c[\"source_id\"]: c for c in chunks}\n\n    claim_sources = []\n    for sentence in re.split(r'(?<=[.!?])\\s+', response_text):\n        markers = re.findall(r'\\[\\d+\\]', sentence)\n        for marker in markers:\n            source_id = citation_map.get(marker)\n            if source_id:\n                chunk = chunk_by_source.get(source_id, {})\n                claim_sources.append({\n                    \"claim_sentence\": sentence.strip(),\n                    \"marker\": marker,\n                    \"source_id\": source_id,\n                    \"source_uri\": chunk.get(\"source_uri\", \"\"),\n                    \"chunk_id\": chunk.get(\"chunk_id\", \"\"),\n                    \"source_version\": chunk.get(\"source_version\", \"\"),\n                })\n    return claim_sources\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Handling Source Retraction"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When a source document is retracted — due to a GDPR deletion request, a policy update, or an error — you must identify every AI response that was grounded in that document and flag or retract those responses."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Retraction Workflow"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
