      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Source provenance for RAG pipelines requires provenance metadata — source_id, chunk_id, content_hash, ACL, and classification — to be attached at ingest and preserved through every stage to the vector store. Access-controlled retrieval filters chunks by the requesting user's roles before they reach Claude's context. Citation markers injected into the context prompt Claude to reference sources explicitly; post-response parsing extracts claim-to-source mappings that compliance officers can inspect. When a source is retracted, query the provenance store to identify all dependent responses and flag them for review. This architecture turns RAG from a black box into an auditable knowledge pipeline."
          }
        ]
